<doc>
  <member name="eAVEncVideoSourceScanType">
    <summary>
      <para>Specifies whether the input frames for an encoder are progressive or interlaced. This enumeration is used with the <a href="https://docs.microsoft.com//windows/desktop/DirectShow/avencvideoforcesourcescantype-property">AVEncVideoForceSourceScanType</a> property.</para>
    </summary>
    <seealso href="https://docs.microsoft.com//windows/desktop/DirectShow/codec-api-enumerations">Codec API Enumerations</seealso>
    <seealso cref="ICodecAPI Interface" />
  </member>
  <member name="eAVEncVideoSourceScanType.eAVEncVideoSourceScan_Automatic">
    <summary>
      <para>Use the media type on the encoder's input pin to determine whether the frames are progressive or interlaced.</para>
    </summary>
  </member>
  <member name="eAVEncVideoSourceScanType.eAVEncVideoSourceScan_Interlaced">
    <summary>
      <para>Input frames are interlaced.</para>
    </summary>
  </member>
  <member name="eAVEncVideoSourceScanType.eAVEncVideoSourceScan_Progressive">
    <summary>
      <para>Input frames are progressive.</para>
    </summary>
  </member>
</doc>